{
  "texts": [
    "To address this, recent advances in graphbased representation learning have introduced new possibilities.",
    "Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) allow the encoding of molecular structures as graphs, where atoms are represented as nodes and chemical bonds as edges.",
    "This enables the model to learn topological and functional relationships directly from chemical structures (Wang et al. 2023).",
    "In the context of olfaction, GNNs have shown promise in chemical odor mapping, which involves predicting odor descriptors from molecular graphs (Sharma et al. 2021).",
    "By modeling how structural motifs relate to perceived smell categories, these networks can uncover nonlinear and high-order dependencies that traditional fingerprint-based models may miss."
  ]
}